{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632891"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:45:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:45:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17447"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17447","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17447"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10137"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70806"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10137"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17447"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56272"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5419"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23805"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70806","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70806"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare-related stigma remains a significant barrier to accessing medical care and achieving optimal health outcomes. It affects how people perceive themselves, how they engage with healthcare services, and how healthcare providers deliver care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary impact of stigma in healthcare settings?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reduces disclosure of symptoms to healthcare providers","Increases self-management of conditions","Delays or prevents appropriate care-seeking behaviour","Promotes use of alternative healthcare services","Leads to overutilisation of emergency services"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary impact of stigma in healthcare settings is that it \u003Cstrong\u003Edelays or prevents appropriate care-seeking behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E. When people feel stigmatised, they often avoid seeking necessary medical care, leading to worse health outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduces disclosure of symptoms to healthcare providers\u003C/strong\u003E: while this is indeed an effect of stigma, it is secondary to the primary impact of delayed care-seeking.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases self-management of conditions\u003C/strong\u003E: while stigmatised individuals may attempt to manage conditions themselves, this is usually inappropriate and leads to worse outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotes use of alternative healthcare services\u003C/strong\u003E: while some may turn to alternative services due to stigma, this is not the primary impact and can be harmful.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeads to overutilisation of emergency services\u003C/strong\u003E: while delayed care can eventually lead to emergency presentations, this is a consequence rather than the primary impact.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStigma can manifest in various ways, including social rejection, discrimination, and negative stereotyping. These experiences can lead to internalised shame, reduced self-esteem, and reluctance to engage with healthcare services.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Stigma in healthcare refers to negative attitudes, beliefs and behaviours directed towards individuals with certain conditions or characteristics.","Healthcare-related stigma can lead to delayed care-seeking, poor adherence to treatment, and worse health outcomes.","Common targets of healthcare stigma include mental illness, obesity, substance use disorders, and certain infectious diseases."],"references":["Nyblade, L., Stockton, M.A., Giger, K. et al. Stigma in health facilities: why it matters and how we can change it. BMC Med 17, 25 (2019). https://doi.org/10.1186/s12916-019-1256-2"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56272"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17447"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56272"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T14:10:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T14:10:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10137"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70806"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"update